## App-Specific Rules — News Feeds / RSS
 
### Instance Storage & Data Model
- Persist configuration and data in instance storage only.
- Required storage keys:
  - `selectedFeeds`: string[]
  - `cachedArticles`: Article[]
  - `lastUpdatedAt`: timestamp
  - `isOffline`: boolean
  - `settings`:
    - `articleDurationSec`
    - `refreshIntervalMin`
    - `transitionStyle`
- Render must subscribe to storage updates.
- Settings may only update configuration values.
 
### Feed Fetching Rules
- RSS/Atom feeds must be fetched using TelemetryOS Proxy API.
- Never use direct `fetch(url)` for external feeds.
- Enforce a fetch timeout (e.g. 30 seconds).
- Fetching must run in a background worker.
- Default refresh interval: 15 minutes.
- Allowed refresh interval range: 5–60 minutes.
 
### Parsing & Normalization
- Normalize all feed items into a single internal `Article` shape.
- Required fields:
  - title
  - description or summary
  - link
  - publishedAt
  - sourceId
- Optional fields:
  - imageUrl
  - sourceLogoUrl
- Skip articles missing a headline or description.
- Truncate overly long text to preserve layout stability.
 
### Rotation & Transitions
- Render must display one article at a time.
- Default article duration: 10 seconds.
- Allowed duration range: 5–60 seconds.
- Articles rotate continuously in a loop.
- New content must not interrupt the currently displayed article.
- Supported transitions:
  - fade
  - slide
  - cut
 
### Offline & Partial Failure Behavior
- If network fails:
  - continue showing cached articles
  - display a subtle “Content may not be current” indicator
- If some feeds fail:
  - skip failed feeds
  - continue rotating available content
- If all feeds fail:
  - show cached content only
- If no feeds are selected:
  - render an empty state message instructing to configure feeds in Settings
 
### Render Layout Rules
- Article card may include:
  - headline (primary focal point)
  - short summary (2–3 sentences)
  - article image (optional)
  - source logo
  - relative timestamp
- Content priority under tight space:
  - P1: headline + source or timestamp
  - P2: summary
  - P3: image and decorative elements
 
### Settings Panel Rules
- Feed selection UI must:
  - show curated feed list
  - group feeds by category
  - support checkbox selection
  - support Select All / Deselect All
  - allow category filtering
- Timing controls must exist:
  - article duration (5–60s)
  - refresh interval (5–60 min)
- Transition style selector must exist:
  - fade
  - slide
  - cut
 
### Curated Feeds Constraint
- Feed list is fixed and curated.
- Do not allow arbitrary RSS URL input.
- Custom URL support belongs to a separate app.